  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Kings 4:8",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Kings 4:8",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Elisha passed to Shunem, where was a great woman — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Great for estate, or birth and quality. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And she constrained him to eat bread — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Pressed him with great importunity, and at length, with great difficulty, prevailed with him to dine with her. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "As oft as he passed by he turned in thither — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "She made him so welcome, that he did not scruple, when he had occasion to go that way, to step in there and refresh himself; which she probably invited him to do.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
